    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc.01484.003_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">Washington D.C.<ptr target="loc.01484_n1"/></name>
                    <date when="1891-04-22">April 22&#8211;1891.</date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>My old friend&#8212;</salute>
            </opener>
            <p>I have been away from home a great deal and have not had time to come
                over when at home. I think of you often and wonder if I can be of any service to you&#8212;all
                you have to do is to "<hi rend="underline">rub</hi> the lamp" and we will answer
                <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="loc.01484.004_large.jpg" type="verso"/>
                <pb xml:id="leaf002r" facs="loc.01484.005_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
                Are we in our usual health?&#8212;Do you need anything? Would
                some good whiskey help out!</p>
            <p>You know myself and family are only too glad to serve you! Drop me at note to Phil at 326. N. 39 st.&#8212;old
                address, and let us know how you are&#8212;and what you need for your comfort.</p>
            <closer>
                <salute>Always yours</salute>
                <signed>Thomas Donaldson</signed>   
            </closer>
            <postscript>
                <p>I am working on a new Indian book! 
                    I don't want you to forget to make some notes on the Catlin Book<ptr target="loc.01484_n2"/>&#8212;</p>
            </postscript>
            <pb xml:id="leaf002v" facs="loc.01484.006_large.jpg" type="verso"/>
            <pb xml:id="leaf003r" facs="loc.01484.001_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <note type="editorial" place="top" resp="#ht">see note Aug 6 1891</note>
            <pb xml:id="leaf003v" facs="loc.01484.002_large.jpg" type="verso"/>
